(secondQuint)Capecitabine in Treating Patients With Recurrent Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, or Primary Peritoneal Cancer.

 OBJECTIVES: I.

 Determine the response rate and time to treatment failure in patients with recurrent ovarian epithelial, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma treated with oral capecitabine.

 II.

 Determine the tolerability and safety of this regimen in these patients.

 OUTLINE: Patients receive oral capecitabine twice daily for 14 days.

 Treatment continues every 3 weeks in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

 PROJECTED ACCRUAL: A total of 14-35 patients will be accrued for this study.

